International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 7 Jan 2015
Source: Pittsburgh Post Gazette [edited]
http://www.post-gazette.com/news/health/2015/01/07/Mumps-outbreak-stumps-Allegheny-County-health-officials/stories/201501070175


An outbreak of mumps in Allegheny County has been confined to the Pittsburgh Penguins organization, health officials said today [7 Jan 2015].

Center Sidney Crosby, defenseman Olli Maatta, right winger Beau Bennett, winger Steve Downie and goalie Thomas Greiss were diagnosed with the disease late last year [2014] that also afflicted players on 4 other National Hockey League teams.

Donald Burke, an infectious disease-trained epidemiologist and member of the county health board, said the outbreak across the league was unusual. "[It] doesn't make a whole lot of epidemiological sense to have such a confined outbreak in what is an adult population of a disease that is normally a childhood disease that is vaccine-preventable," he said.

Eight separate specimens from the county were sent to a state lab for testing but came back negative for mumps, said health department medical epidemiologist Kristen Mertz. Although causing discomfort, mumps only rarely leads to serious complications, according to health officials.

Classes at Sharpsville Area School District in Mercer County were canceled Monday [5 Jan 2015] as a precaution against 2 suspected cases of the mumps.

[Byline: Molly Born]

