[For a discussion of mumps, see my comments in ProMED-mail post Mumps - USA: (OH) university students 20140308.2321285.

Mumps outbreaks even among vaccinated populations have been reported frequently during recent years, especially among college students where the intensity of exposure among students was presumed to have overcome the vaccine-induced immunity (http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/20/4/13-1681_article.htm).

The Pittsburgh Penguins are a professional ice hockey team based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pittsburgh_Penguins). They are members of the National Hockey League (NHL). Pittsburgh is the seat of Allegheny County and, with a population of 305 841 is the 2nd-largest city in the U.S. state of Pennsylvania in the mid-Atlantic region of the U.S. (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pittsburgh). - Mod.ML

